00:00:44.240 --> 00:00:49.000
Sid: Hello. I'm Sid Roth your investigative
reporter. Angry!

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:51.300
And he had reason to be angry.

00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:55.219
My guest, Mike Schwartz, was angry.

00:00:55.219 --> 00:00:57.480
His father left before he was born.

00:00:57.480 --> 00:01:02.240
I mean, you almost were raised “angry at
the world”.

00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:06.020
Mike: I really can't remember a time when
I wasn't angry, and I didn't want to be.

00:01:06.020 --> 00:01:10.300
You know, it was - I wouldn't say it was funny,
but I didn't want to be angry.

00:01:10.300 --> 00:01:17.570
But it was there - maybe the rejection - and
I couldn't understand it.

00:01:17.570 --> 00:01:21.050
It didn't seem like I was able to do good.

00:01:21.050 --> 00:01:25.070
And when I was younger, you know, everybody
thought I was the kid that most was likely

00:01:25.070 --> 00:01:26.820
to die a horrible death at 18.

00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:28.480
Sid: Did people say that in your presence?

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:28.980
Mike: Yes.

00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:32.560
Sid: Not that specifically, but just “You'll
never amount to anything.”

00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:35.380
Mike: Yes. My family did that. It was curses.

00:01:35.380 --> 00:01:40.800
Many times it was I - they had a cuss word
for me that I won't repeat.

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:46.680
But it was - that was what they called me,
and it was hard.

00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:48.000
It takes its toll.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.540
Sid: Did it bother that you didn't have a
father when you were growing up?

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:56.560
Mike: Now I'm realizing that it did.

00:01:56.560 --> 00:02:00.080
Back then, you know, when you're going through
it you don't know that this is not normal,

00:02:00.080 --> 00:02:01.600
because it's normal for you.

00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:02.690
Yeah, it bothered me.

00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:05.580
Sid: Did you get into crime? Drugs?

00:02:05.580 --> 00:02:06.770
Mike: I was into everything.

00:02:06.770 --> 00:02:09.840
I was continually in trouble.

00:02:09.840 --> 00:02:15.530
I probably had 50 arrests; spent a couple
of years in jails.

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:20.680
I was into every kind of drug there is except
- I don't know why I never got into heroin,

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:22.280
because I thought it was a dead man's drug.

00:02:22.280 --> 00:02:23.430
But everything else was, too.

00:02:23.430 --> 00:02:24.470
Sid: Well you thought, “Right”.

00:02:24.470 --> 00:02:25.470
Mike: Yeah.

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:30.490
I was into drugs you could do, and I was into
every sort of perversion with men and women.

00:02:30.490 --> 00:02:31.760
It didn't matter.

00:02:31.760 --> 00:02:39.000
Sid: I have noticed that a lot of people that
have bad fathers or no fathers, somehow

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:43.920
they fall into the trap of homosexuality;
there seems to be a pattern.

00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:44.480
Mike: Yeah.

00:02:44.480 --> 00:02:48.840
I don't know about that, but I know where
I was, and it just seems like that when things

00:02:48.840 --> 00:02:53.240
open up, there's nothing holy about anything
anymore.

00:02:53.240 --> 00:02:58.000
And I had - I had no hope.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:03.530
But there was something inside me, since I
was kid, that I would lay at night and cry.

00:03:03.530 --> 00:03:08.570
When I'd hear about this person named Jesus,
I would cry, and I didn't understand it.

00:03:08.570 --> 00:03:15.310
I was raised Catholic, but nobody told me
about salvation, you know.

00:03:15.310 --> 00:03:18.960
Nobody explained to me any of that stuff for
years.

00:03:18.960 --> 00:03:20.900
And I'd lay at night and cry, you know.

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:25.209
I'd hear a whistle blow, and every night this
train would go by, and the whistle would blow,

00:03:25.209 --> 00:03:28.400
and I'd cry and I'd say, “God, I want to
be good.

00:03:28.400 --> 00:03:29.580
Why can't I be good?”

00:03:29.580 --> 00:03:32.520
This is - was since I was eight, nine-years
old.

00:03:32.520 --> 00:03:35.300
Sid: Why did you join the military service?

00:03:35.300 --> 00:03:38.140
Mike: It was either join the military or go
to jail.

00:03:38.140 --> 00:03:38.640
Sid: Really?

00:03:38.640 --> 00:03:39.680
Mike: Yes, sir.

00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:42.959
Back in the Vietnam days they needed all the
help they could get.

00:03:42.959 --> 00:03:48.450
So I lived in Chicago, and I was just involved
in some more trouble.

00:03:48.450 --> 00:03:52.680
And they gave us a choice back then to go
in the Army or go to jail.

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:56.660
And back then, John Wayne was popular, and
you didn't think bullets could kill you.

00:03:56.660 --> 00:04:00.490
You know? it was like this glorious thing to
kill, and it’s was not that way.

00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.460
Sid: Vietnam was not fun.

00:04:02.460 --> 00:04:06.700
Mike: Vietnam was a horror, a horrible
nightmare.

00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:09.820
There's nothing glorious about it.

00:04:11.020 --> 00:04:13.700
Sid: You had some pretty close calls.

00:04:13.700 --> 00:04:16.280
Mike: There is nothing glorious about killing
anybody.

00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:19.080
That's the devil.

00:04:19.080 --> 00:04:27.240
We got overrun on June 6, 1966, and I was
trying to find this other personnel carrier

00:04:27.240 --> 00:04:31.200
that got blown up, and it was on fire.

00:04:31.200 --> 00:04:32.560
So somebody had to go over there.

00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:37.240
I'm not a hero, but sometimes you just do
heroic things.

00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:43.160
And on the way there I ran into three North
Vietnamese.

00:04:43.160 --> 00:04:48.380
I was crawling on my hands and knees with
a 45 in my belt, and I hit them with my head

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:49.860
on their knees.

00:04:49.860 --> 00:04:56.280
And I looked up and I remember saying, “Oh
God, I'm dead.”

00:04:56.280 --> 00:05:01.730
And when that happened, they looked down at
me, and they pointed their finger at me and

00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:04.210
started laughing.

00:05:04.210 --> 00:05:07.480
And I felt this strange presence.

00:05:09.760 --> 00:05:13.220
They just walked off.

00:05:13.220 --> 00:05:15.780
They shot the machine gun in the air and walked
off.

00:05:15.780 --> 00:05:18.380
Sid: That doesn't make any sense to me, Mike.

00:05:18.380 --> 00:05:20.980
How could that happen?

00:05:20.980 --> 00:05:21.740
Mike: I don't know.

00:05:21.740 --> 00:05:25.320
I mean, I know why it happened now; I didn't
know then.

00:05:25.320 --> 00:05:28.140
Sid: What did you think when it happened,
“You're lucky?”

00:05:28.140 --> 00:05:29.160
Mike: Yeah.

00:05:29.160 --> 00:05:29.660
Yeah.

00:05:29.660 --> 00:05:30.160
Really.

00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:35.040
And then there was a voice said to me that
tormented me later.

00:05:35.040 --> 00:05:40.810
This voice said to me, "You're not even good
enough to go to Hell”, and that hurt me

00:05:40.810 --> 00:05:41.500
worse.

00:05:41.500 --> 00:05:47.220
That really - it was like the rejection stronghold
that was in me, and the self-pity; it just

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:48.460
ate that up.

00:05:48.460 --> 00:05:52.240
Sid: You think you're rejected.

00:05:52.240 --> 00:05:56.720
You think the world has treated you badly.

00:05:56.720 --> 00:06:03.660
Well you're looking at a man that never knew
anything but rejection.

00:06:03.660 --> 00:06:06.040
And I'm going to tell you something.

00:06:06.040 --> 00:06:10.160
It was supernatural: Three men ready to shoot
you and -

00:06:10.169 --> 00:06:11.229
Mike: They were killing everybody.

00:06:11.229 --> 00:06:15.180
There was already a hundred wounded and 20
dead on the ground, and we were overrun.

00:06:15.180 --> 00:06:21.710
There was a hundred, 120 of us, and there
was, oh, 1,500, 2,000 of them.

00:06:21.710 --> 00:06:25.400
And they ambushed us in the swamps, and they
killed; they were killing everybody.

00:06:25.400 --> 00:06:28.480
Just about everybody was wounded or hurt,
and we're pinned down, and we couldn't get

00:06:28.480 --> 00:06:30.220
any help.

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:33.400
And I was miraculously saved.

00:06:33.400 --> 00:06:35.560
Sid: So you survive Vietnam.

00:06:35.560 --> 00:06:36.060
Mike: Yes.

00:06:36.060 --> 00:06:36.980
Sid: You come back.

00:06:36.980 --> 00:06:41.140
And tell me about that day you went to the
gym.

00:06:41.140 --> 00:06:46.820
Mike: Well years later, I went to the gym,
and this guy was messing with me.

00:06:46.820 --> 00:06:53.100
He had this "I Love Jesus" t-shirt on, and
he kept bugging me and bugging me.

00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:55.871
Sid: But you liked Jesus, so why would that
bother you?

00:06:55.871 --> 00:06:58.020
Mike: Well because I was full of demonic stuff.

00:06:58.020 --> 00:07:02.401
I wasn't - when you're not living for the
King, then you're going to, you know, you're

00:07:02.401 --> 00:07:06.980
going to reject anybody that's acting like
they love Him.

00:07:06.980 --> 00:07:11.080
And they were - this man was presenting something
to me that was real.

00:07:11.080 --> 00:07:17.139
I mean, I was 33 or 34-years old and never
had been presented with the Gospel, in America.

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:22.180
Never been told about Jesus was Lord, and
He could take away your sins and remove them

00:07:22.180 --> 00:07:23.600
- any of that; nothing.

00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:25.720
Nobody has ever confronted me.

00:07:25.720 --> 00:07:27.080
Sid: So he was confronting you.

00:07:27.080 --> 00:07:28.910
Mike: He was confronting me, and I was running.

00:07:28.910 --> 00:07:32.190
But there was something that kept bringing
us together.

00:07:32.190 --> 00:07:37.460
And he was speaking things into my life.

00:07:38.060 --> 00:07:41.700
Sid: But I'm talking about the time that you
hurt your back.

00:07:41.700 --> 00:07:43.600
Mike: Well this was right after that.

00:07:43.600 --> 00:07:45.490
Well this guy was a power lifter.

00:07:45.490 --> 00:07:46.600
He was a Christian.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:54.880
So I decided, “Well I'm going to be a power
lifter”, so I put my soul into it, and I

00:07:54.880 --> 00:07:59.960
crushed - I was doing deep squats, and I crushed
- I never came out of them.

00:07:59.960 --> 00:08:01.070
I went down and never came out.

00:08:01.070 --> 00:08:02.420
I just crushed my spine.

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:03.530
Sid: Oh my goodness.

00:08:03.530 --> 00:08:04.650
Can you picture that?

00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:06.260
He's almost like an accordion.

00:08:06.260 --> 00:08:10.440
He crushes his spine with those heavy weights
in the gym.

00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:11.740
We'll pick up right here.

00:08:11.740 --> 00:08:13.280
Don't go away.

