00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:48.760
Sid: Hello. Sid Roth your investigative
reporter here with Mike Schwartz.

00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:53.819
And oh, we're having so much fun in between
during the break.

00:15:53.820 --> 00:15:56.240
We're going to go to Janie in the control
room.

00:15:56.240 --> 00:16:01.880
Janie, Mike has just told me that he has gotten
drunk in the spirit.

00:16:01.880 --> 00:16:06.699
The Spirit of God is falling on him so much
and he said before this is over, I'm going

00:16:06.700 --> 00:16:11.340
to get drunk and who's on for next week, before
I get drunk?

00:16:11.340 --> 00:16:13.740
Janie: I think that's about to happen to me.

00:16:13.740 --> 00:16:17.760
Well you'll be interviewing a man, another
man who was full of rage.

00:16:17.760 --> 00:16:23.840
But this man had detailed plans of murdering
masses of white people.

00:16:23.840 --> 00:16:27.820
He related to black Muslims and Malcom X.

00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:30.020
But something happened in his car.

00:16:30.020 --> 00:16:36.040
He heard something and it made this man full
of hate love all people.

00:16:36.040 --> 00:16:40.240
Sid: It sounds to me like it's the same type
of thing that's just happened to Mike Schwartz.

00:16:40.240 --> 00:16:49.360
Mike, God says that you, today, you must accept
Him or it will be too late.

00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:50.700
What were His exact words?

00:16:50.700 --> 00:16:57.040
Mike: His exact words is, "Michael," he says,
"I want you to give Me your heart, or I will

00:16:57.040 --> 00:17:02.600
lift My spirit off you and you will go to
Hell."

00:17:02.600 --> 00:17:09.120
And I'm at the rush hour in Kansas City traffic
on a Friday, and people - and I'm beating

00:17:09.120 --> 00:17:17.000
the dashboard out of this car, just - and
just - and He said that to me three times.

00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:20.720
And I said, “No”, the third time, and
I started to say it the fourth time; I was

00:17:20.720 --> 00:17:23.040
going to go now, and I said -
Sid: Wait.

00:17:23.040 --> 00:17:25.540
Why would you say “No” to God?

00:17:25.540 --> 00:17:26.800
God, who saved your life?

00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:29.280
God, the only one that really loved you?

00:17:29.280 --> 00:17:30.760
Why would you say “No” to Him?

00:17:30.760 --> 00:17:36.620
Mike: Well I guess all anger and bitterness,
and resentment stems back, and it goes back

00:17:36.620 --> 00:17:40.870
to the one that can control everything is
God, if you know it or not.

00:17:40.870 --> 00:17:45.420
Now I know I was bitter and angry at Him,
and I didn't trust Him.

00:17:45.420 --> 00:17:46.360
Why should I?

00:17:46.360 --> 00:17:51.000
I felt like I had been dealt a bad set of
cards, and you know, this is the way you feel.

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:52.020
This is not the truth.

00:17:52.020 --> 00:17:54.060
Sid: The truth is you did have a tough life.

00:17:54.060 --> 00:17:54.920
Mike: Oh yeah.

00:17:54.920 --> 00:17:58.660
But I have a testimony, too, and Jesus rescued
me.

00:17:58.660 --> 00:18:00.240
Sid: Tell me what happened.

00:18:00.240 --> 00:18:05.980
Mike: Well the fourth time I said “Yes”.

00:18:05.980 --> 00:18:10.920
And I broke, and I cried, and I beat the dash
up.

00:18:10.920 --> 00:18:15.460
And I said to Him, “Okay”, and He said,
"Repeat after Me."

00:18:15.460 --> 00:18:16.180
Sid: He said that?

00:18:16.180 --> 00:18:17.520
Mike: He said, "Repeat after Me."

00:18:17.520 --> 00:18:19.560
Sid: Wait. I usually say that.

00:18:19.560 --> 00:18:22.300
God said that to him, "Repeat after me."

00:18:22.300 --> 00:18:23.300
What did He tell you to repeat?

00:18:23.300 --> 00:18:30.070
Mike: He said, "I want you to give Me your
heart, your mind, your body, your life, your

00:18:30.070 --> 00:18:35.970
future, and let Me do what I want to do with
it."

00:18:35.970 --> 00:18:37.160
I didn't even think I had that.

00:18:37.160 --> 00:18:39.880
I didn't know that was available as a human
being.

00:18:39.880 --> 00:18:41.790
I just was looking for the pit.

00:18:41.790 --> 00:18:43.200
And I said, "Yes, God."

00:18:43.200 --> 00:18:49.360
And He said a couple of other things that
I can't remember now that were anti-selfishness.

00:18:49.360 --> 00:18:52.660
And then He said to me - and I thought I was
done.

00:18:53.740 --> 00:18:57.900
And He said to me - this is the God I know
- "P.S."

00:18:57.900 --> 00:19:00.040
I says, "What?"

00:19:00.040 --> 00:19:04.060
He said, "Michael, no conditions."

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:07.440
He says, "You have to drop every one of your
conditions."

00:19:07.440 --> 00:19:14.120
And I said, "Jesus, I'll go anywhere, do anything,
no matter what it is, what it means.

00:19:14.120 --> 00:19:15.920
Your will be done."

00:19:15.920 --> 00:19:19.980
And my life instantly changed in that car.

00:19:19.980 --> 00:19:23.100
No more drugs, no more drinking, no more women.

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:23.820
Instantly.

00:19:23.820 --> 00:19:24.460
Sid: Instantly?

00:19:24.460 --> 00:19:26.660
No withdrawals from anything.

00:19:26.660 --> 00:19:31.820
Sid: No, but physiologically, that's not
possible. [Laughs]

00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:33.700
Mike: Yeah, exactly.

00:19:33.700 --> 00:19:34.900
And I went home.

00:19:34.900 --> 00:19:40.660
I went back, and I went back and my wife,
who is my wife now, looked at me and

00:19:40.660 --> 00:19:43.640
she says, "What happened to you?"

00:19:44.240 --> 00:19:45.020
Sid: She could see.

00:19:45.020 --> 00:19:46.020
Mike: Oh yeah.

00:19:46.020 --> 00:19:49.000
I was a different "coot"; I was a different
"coot".

00:19:49.000 --> 00:19:52.160
There was even a measure of some peace for
the first time.

00:19:52.160 --> 00:19:54.380
I was “wired for sound”.

00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:59.300
And yeah, I had a conversion experience.

00:19:59.300 --> 00:20:03.720
When the King of Glory comes in your heart,
things have to change.

00:20:03.720 --> 00:20:05.730
I mean, you just can't go on the way you were.

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:07.720
There has to be something different.

00:20:07.720 --> 00:20:09.020
Sid: God is so good.

00:20:09.020 --> 00:20:09.680
Mike: Amen.

00:20:09.680 --> 00:20:11.800
Sid: God is so good. I mean, He didn't give
up on you.

00:20:11.800 --> 00:20:13.030
You gave up on the world.

00:20:13.030 --> 00:20:14.030
You gave up on God.

00:20:14.030 --> 00:20:14.520
Mike: Yeah.

00:20:14.520 --> 00:20:15.440
Sid: But He didn't give up you.

00:20:15.440 --> 00:20:15.940
Mike: No.

00:20:15.940 --> 00:20:17.820
Sid: And He didn't give up on you.

00:20:17.820 --> 00:20:20.080
He did not give up on you.

00:20:20.080 --> 00:20:23.280
Why do you think you're watching this right
now?

00:20:23.280 --> 00:20:30.100
Now they're going to be very upset with me,
Mike, if you don't tell me about supernatural

00:20:30.100 --> 00:20:31.500
transportation.

00:20:31.500 --> 00:20:35.280
Mike: Well I figured this was normal transportation
for Christians.

00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:37.120
It's in the scriptures.

00:20:37.120 --> 00:20:37.620
Sid: It is.

00:20:37.620 --> 00:20:38.400
Mike: It is.

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:41.360
And you don't hear a lot of it, and it's not
my fault.

00:20:41.360 --> 00:20:47.011
And what I want to say is I had nothing to
do with this transportation problem, and I

00:20:47.020 --> 00:20:49.560
didn't -
Sid: Describe one time.

00:20:49.560 --> 00:20:51.940
Mike: Jesus told us to go to England.

00:20:51.940 --> 00:20:54.940
I told a friend, and the Lord told him to
go.

00:20:54.940 --> 00:20:59.500
We went to England, and we got in this car
with these English people - this van - and

00:20:59.500 --> 00:21:06.420
we're going down the motorway, and the van
fills up with smoke, or looked like smoke.

00:21:06.420 --> 00:21:10.460
Well we were - we weren't alive, it didn't
feel like.

00:21:10.460 --> 00:21:17.240
And we're listening to worship, and then time
quit.

00:21:17.240 --> 00:21:23.620
And the next thing I knew, we like come to,
and we're a hundred kilometers down the motorway.

00:21:23.620 --> 00:21:24.620
Sid: Instantly?

00:21:24.620 --> 00:21:26.720
Mike: Well I don't know.

00:21:26.720 --> 00:21:31.090
When I went out and when I -
Sid: Were you driving the car?

00:21:31.090 --> 00:21:33.090
Mike: No. I was watching the guy driving it.

00:21:33.090 --> 00:21:34.180
It didn't look like he could drive either.

00:21:34.180 --> 00:21:35.480
He kind of was just distorted.

00:21:35.480 --> 00:21:37.440
He just - I asked him later what happened.

00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:40.080
He said, "I don't know how I drove.

00:21:40.080 --> 00:21:42.360
The car just filled up."

00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:43.820
Sid: Filled up with smoke.

00:21:43.820 --> 00:21:50.940
Mike: Yeah, smoke or a cloud, or something;
something white.

00:21:50.940 --> 00:21:55.500
We were just worshiping, and all of a sudden
we were a hundred miles down the motorway.

00:21:55.500 --> 00:21:57.040
Sid: Has this happened more than once?

00:21:57.040 --> 00:21:58.040
Mike: Three or four times.

00:21:58.040 --> 00:22:00.930
It just happened a month ago when I was hunting.

00:22:00.930 --> 00:22:04.400
Well it happened on the way from Texas to
Oklahoma.

00:22:04.400 --> 00:22:09.320
I was looking at a road sign at 7:00 in the
morning, and I had an appointment at eight,

00:22:09.320 --> 00:22:12.700
so I figured if I drive so many miles an hour
I could make it.

00:22:12.700 --> 00:22:18.800
And the roadside said 62 miles an hour, and
had - it was exactly seven.

00:22:18.800 --> 00:22:22.560
I was wide awake and I had my family in the
car.

00:22:22.560 --> 00:22:31.400
And all of a sudden I felt this strange, like,
wind blow through me, and I heard somebody

00:22:31.400 --> 00:22:32.960
laugh.

00:22:32.960 --> 00:22:37.060
And I kind of - and it's like I knew it was
Jesus.

00:22:37.060 --> 00:22:39.180
I says, “What's the deal?”

00:22:39.180 --> 00:22:45.180
And I looked over at the road sign; it said
20 miles to Wichita.

00:22:45.180 --> 00:22:49.240
I looked at my watch and I says, "Uh-oh, 16
minutes.

00:22:49.240 --> 00:22:51.010
You can't do it.

00:22:51.010 --> 00:22:54.750
You can’t; it's impossible."

00:22:54.750 --> 00:22:55.880
And it's just like he was laughing.

00:22:55.880 --> 00:22:57.230
And I says, "Why did you do that?"

00:22:57.230 --> 00:22:59.800
And He says, "I felt like it."

00:22:59.800 --> 00:23:05.240
And then He told me, He says in the End-Times
this is going to be the mode of transportation

00:23:05.240 --> 00:23:07.160
for his church.

00:23:07.160 --> 00:23:12.800
He says when you think you can't go somewhere
because of what's coming up trouble," He says,

00:23:12.800 --> 00:23:14.340
"I don't need airplane tickets.

00:23:14.350 --> 00:23:15.820
I don't need money."

00:23:15.820 --> 00:23:19.300
He says, "I'll just send whoever I want to
send wherever I want to send them."

00:23:19.300 --> 00:23:22.680
He says, "This is my mode of transportation."

00:23:22.680 --> 00:23:27.300
And then a month ago I was in the mountains
hunting with two friends, and there's this

00:23:27.300 --> 00:23:29.680
winding road that I hated.

00:23:29.680 --> 00:23:32.200
It's just washboard, and I hate it.

00:23:32.200 --> 00:23:37.780
It's the end of the day, and we didn't kill
our buck, and I just [grunt].

00:23:37.780 --> 00:23:41.420
All of a sudden, I'm on the bottom of the
road, and I feel this thing go through me

00:23:41.420 --> 00:23:42.140
again.

00:23:42.140 --> 00:23:45.480
By now I recognize it; it's about the third
or fourth time.

00:23:45.480 --> 00:23:50.420
I look over to my friends and I says, "How
did we miss all the bumps?"

00:23:50.420 --> 00:23:54.020
And he looked at me and he says, "We didn't,"
he says, “We didn't go through all that

00:23:54.030 --> 00:23:55.030
stuff, did we?"

00:23:55.030 --> 00:23:56.030
I says, “No.”

00:23:56.030 --> 00:23:57.250
I says, "Did we drive by all the stuff?"

00:23:57.250 --> 00:23:59.680
He says, “No.”

00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:03.180
And I knew the Lord, you know - it was three
miles down the hill.

00:24:03.180 --> 00:24:04.000
Sid: And you just instantly?

00:24:04.000 --> 00:24:05.000
Mike: I was just there.

00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:06.180
Sid: How about that?

00:24:06.180 --> 00:24:08.200
(SHWOOP) Just there.

00:24:08.200 --> 00:24:09.700
But that doesn't mean a thing.

00:24:09.700 --> 00:24:12.440
I'm going to tell you what means something.

00:24:12.440 --> 00:24:17.880
Knowing God for yourself, knowing He loves
you, knowing that you could not have gotten

00:24:17.880 --> 00:24:22.680
to this point without Him protecting you.

00:24:22.680 --> 00:24:29.920
Maybe it's not as obvious as Mike, but he
has supernaturally protected you for right

00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:31.740
now.

00:24:31.740 --> 00:24:33.760
Repent of your sins.

00:24:33.760 --> 00:24:43.640
Ask Jesus to forgive you, and in the name
of Jesus, ask God to be your Father.

00:24:43.640 --> 00:24:45.300
You need a father.

00:24:45.300 --> 00:24:50.200
You need a father that loves you; not for
what you do, but who you are.

00:24:50.200 --> 00:24:51.540
He loves you.

00:24:51.540 --> 00:24:53.260
God really loves you.

00:24:53.260 --> 00:24:54.400
He's your Father.

00:24:54.400 --> 00:24:55.420
He really is.

00:24:55.420 --> 00:25:02.800
[music]

